EXPENSE TRACKER APPLICATION
Full Stack Product Documentation

1. Project Overview
Expense Tracker is a full-stack web application used to manage and analyze personal expenses.
It supports CRUD operations and provides analytics for better financial tracking.

Tech Stack:
Frontend: Streamlit
Backend: FastAPI
Database: MySQL

2. System Architecture

            ┌──────────────────────┐
            │   Streamlit UI       │
            │   (Frontend)         │
            └─────────┬────────────┘
                      │ HTTP Requests (requests)
                      ▼
            ┌──────────────────────┐
            │   FastAPI Backend    │
            │   REST API Server    │
            └─────────┬────────────┘
                      │ SQL Queries
                      ▼
            ┌──────────────────────┐
            │     MySQL DB         │
            └──────────────────────┘

            3. Frontend (Streamlit)
3.Frontend(streamlit)
Frontend provides an interactive UI for users to manage expenses and communicates with backend APIs.
Features:
Add Expense
View Expense
Update Expense
Delete Expense
Search by Category
Sort Expenses
Filter Expenses
Analyze Spending (Chart + Summary)
API Used:
POST /add_expense
GET /get_expenses
PUT /update_expense/{id}
DELETE /delete_expense/{id}
GET /search_expense
GET /sort_expenses
GET /filter_expenses
GET /analyze_expenses
Libraries:
Streamlit
Pandas
Requests

4. Backend (FastAPI)
Backend handles business logic and database operations using REST APIs.
Features:
CRUD operations
Sorting & Filtering
Data analytics (SUM, AVG, GROUP BY)
MySQL integration
Database Schema
expense_id (Primary Key)
title (VARCHAR)
amount (DECIMAL)
category (VARCHAR)
created_at (TIMESTAMP)
API Endpoints:
POST /add_expense
GET /get_expenses
PUT /update_expense/{id}
DELETE /delete_expense/{id}
GET /search_expense
GET /sort_expenses
GET /filter_expenses
GET /analyze_expenses
Libraries:
FastAPI
MySQL Connector
Python

6.Conclusion
This project demonstrates a full-stack expense tracking system with API integration, 
database handling, and data visualization.
